The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Bilt net profit rises 31% to Rs 62 cr

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 Paper power

 New Delhi, Jan. 19: Ballarpur Industries Ltd (Bilt) today said its earnings surged 31.12 per cent for the quarter ended December 31, 2006. 

 During the quarter, the companys profits increased to Rs 62.1 crore from Rs 47.4 crore a year ago. Net sales rose 26.40 per cent to Rs 148 crore from Rs 109.2 crore a year ago. Total income rose 26.18 per cent to Rs 553 crore from Rs 438.3 crore in the same period of the previous fiscal. 

 Earnings per share (diluted) for the quarter rose from 83 paise a share to Rs 3.74. 

 The company approved the allotment of 3,544,141 equity shares of Rs 10 each in the quarter. The shares have been allotted on part conversion of foreign currency convertible bonds (FCCBs) of $45 million, which were allotted in November 2003. 

 Total paper sales during the quarter was 1,15,603 tonnes compared with 99,466 tonnes, while production stood at 1,14,723 tonnes against 1,00,372 tonnes a year ago.

 For the half year ended December, the PAT stood at Rs 120.4 crore, up 31.45 per cent from the corresponding period of the previous year.

 Dabur net

 Dabur India Ltd recorded a 24 per cent growth in net profit to Rs 71.73 crore from Rs 57.97 crore in the same period of the previous year. 

 Its turnover increased 26 per cent to Rs 508.70 crore from Rs 404.84 crore a year ago.

 Total income rose to Rs 620.86 crore in the quarter ended December 31, against Rs 543 crore in the previous fiscal.

 The key drivers of growth were international business, foods, oral care, health supplements and home care, all of which recorded strong double-digit growth. The company is also moving forward on its plan to expand its existing product categories and new geographies, said Sunil Duggal, CEO of Dabur India.

 The companys consolidated net profit in the quarter rose 22.08 per cent to Rs 79.27 crore, while consolidated turnover in the quarter was Rs 617.59 crore, up 14.92 per cent.

 i-flex result

 i-flex solutions today reported a 57 per cent rise in net profit to Rs 91.05 crore in the quarter ended December 31, from Rs 57.95 crore a year ago.

 Revenues grew 33 per cent to Rs 395.56 crore against Rs 297.47 crore in the previous fiscal, the company informed the Bombay Stock Exchange.

 The combined Oracle/i-flex force is already making a difference in winning several top tier names as customers, i-flex chairman and managing director Rajesh Hukku said. 




